WEBVTT

00:04.480 --> 00:07.390
- What'd she say?
- It's complicated.

00:07.390 --> 00:09.820
- I know you.
You didn't talk to her.

00:09.820 --> 00:11.820
- Six years together,
she's just not gonna

00:11.830 --> 00:14.360
give me the thumbs up
to move on.

00:14.360 --> 00:16.630
I'm strategizing.

00:16.630 --> 00:18.460
- Me too.

00:20.630 --> 00:22.130
- Where are you going?

00:22.140 --> 00:24.700
- It's complicated.

00:36.850 --> 00:38.720
- Well, there's not
much to tell.

00:38.720 --> 00:41.950
My secretary and I were sitting
there, preparing for a meeting

00:41.960 --> 00:45.590
and then... no, not now... and then
she goes to the bathroom

00:45.590 --> 00:46.860
and then all of the sudden,
the water just from above...

00:46.860 --> 00:49.130
- lemont's kind of
a sleepy town.

00:49.130 --> 00:50.760
This is my first dead body.

00:50.760 --> 00:53.130
- We can ship a couple of our
overflow up here if you want.

00:53.130 --> 00:54.930
- I'm in charge.
Captain fogarty.

00:54.930 --> 00:56.830
- Oh, nagel, Dawson.
Thanks for calling.

00:56.840 --> 00:59.940
- Under the circumstances,
I figure this is your ballpark.

00:59.940 --> 01:03.140
Manager said that he made
the reservation online.

01:03.140 --> 01:06.410
- Not even when he checked in?
- Didn't have to.

01:06.410 --> 01:09.480
Keycard on the door,
changes for every new customer.

01:09.480 --> 01:10.880
Wallet was in his pocket.

01:10.880 --> 01:12.820
- Any security footage?
- People who come here

01:12.820 --> 01:14.550
don't really want
a record of it.

01:14.550 --> 01:16.420
- In here?

01:22.630 --> 01:25.000
- Yeah, I'd say he's dead.

01:25.000 --> 01:27.500
- Mm-hmm.

01:27.500 --> 01:29.030
- Here.

01:31.170 --> 01:32.740
Excuse me?

01:32.740 --> 01:37.740
- I figured I could
learn something.

01:37.740 --> 01:40.980
Slit wrists.
Pretty obvious suicide.

01:40.980 --> 01:42.910
- Nope. Nothing.

01:42.920 --> 01:46.220
Hot water. Whoever did this
wanted the body to decompose.

01:46.220 --> 01:47.690
- What do you mean,
whoever did this?

01:47.690 --> 01:50.490
He did it.
- Look again, officer.

01:50.490 --> 01:51.660
What's missing?

01:54.930 --> 02:00.600
- A knife.

02:00.600 --> 02:02.800
- Maybe officer jonesy will
get us a cup of coffee

02:02.800 --> 02:04.540
while we discuss the case.

02:04.540 --> 02:06.500
- That's one hell of a way
for a cop to go.

02:06.510 --> 02:08.039
- Yeah.

02:08.039 --> 02:09.940
- Excuse me, I'm sorry.
Did you just say

02:09.940 --> 02:11.480
the victim was a cop?

02:11.480 --> 02:13.480
- Your boss didn't tell you?

02:13.480 --> 02:18.020
Officer jonesy,
meet officer Ted Cody,

02:18.020 --> 02:19.820
Chicago pd.

02:28.860 --> 02:32.060
- Cause of dead, broken neck.

02:32.070 --> 02:34.530
Judging by these severe
cervical vertebral fractures,

02:34.530 --> 02:36.970
I'd say officer Cody
was face down,

02:36.970 --> 02:39.200
the killer put a knee here and...

02:39.210 --> 02:41.540
Snapped his head back.

02:41.540 --> 02:43.070
- And the ankles?
- Can't say.

02:43.080 --> 02:44.980
Maybe when he hit the tub.

02:44.980 --> 02:48.650
Also, he was Mike tysoned.
- The guy bit his ear?

02:48.650 --> 02:50.550
- Someone with
very strong fingers

02:50.550 --> 02:53.550
did a grab, pull and rip.

02:53.550 --> 02:55.250
No pulmonary edema,
minimal bleeding,

02:55.260 --> 02:57.150
he was dead before
his wrists were cut

02:57.160 --> 02:58.520
and was dumped into the tub.

02:58.530 --> 03:00.190
- So someone went to
a lot of trouble

03:00.190 --> 03:02.230
to make us think
that this was a suicide.

03:02.230 --> 03:03.660
- Like we're gonna miss
a broken neck.

03:03.660 --> 03:05.600
- Us, no.
But the locals might.

03:05.600 --> 03:07.600
- See the jagged nature
of the cuts?

03:07.600 --> 03:10.230
I'd say we're looking at
a bread knife.

03:10.240 --> 03:11.540
Something like that.

03:11.540 --> 03:14.070
- Because the body
was in hot water,

03:14.070 --> 03:17.040
I'd say the tod was sometime
around noon yesterday.

03:17.040 --> 03:18.540
Give or take.

03:18.550 --> 03:19.540
- Okay.
- Thanks, joy.

03:19.550 --> 03:21.310
- Oh, it gets better.

03:21.310 --> 03:24.050
Officer Cody had
pancreatic cancer.

03:24.050 --> 03:27.650
He didn't have more than
six weeks left on this planet.

03:27.650 --> 03:30.590
We found traces of gemcitabine
oxaliplatin... that's chemo...

03:30.590 --> 03:33.260
Along with some alcohol
in his blood.

03:33.260 --> 03:36.890
That's a big no-no.

03:36.900 --> 03:38.260
- I always thought
I'd get that call

03:38.260 --> 03:40.000
in the middle of the night,
you know?

03:40.000 --> 03:43.070
Shot on duty, car accident.

03:43.070 --> 03:45.140
Suicide never even
crossed my mind.

03:45.140 --> 03:49.010
I guess it makes sense,
with the pain and medicines.

03:49.010 --> 03:51.610
Bills piling up.
- I'm sorry, Mrs. Cody.

03:51.610 --> 03:54.250
Nobody told you?
- Told me what?

03:54.250 --> 03:58.180
- Your husband...
- Former husband.

03:58.180 --> 04:00.120
- We're thinking he may have
been murdered.

04:04.290 --> 04:08.290
He was a selfish prick, okay?

04:08.290 --> 04:10.330
He insisted on dying alone.

04:10.330 --> 04:12.600
Soon as he was diagnosed,
he moved out.

04:12.600 --> 04:15.600
- When was that?
- Eight months ago.

04:15.600 --> 04:17.100
- I don't even know
what I'm gonna do for money.

04:17.100 --> 04:21.610
I just... he was giving me
1,200 a month in cash.

04:21.610 --> 04:26.080
He was working another job to
help with tj... that's our son.

04:26.080 --> 04:28.610
- You okay, mom?

04:28.620 --> 04:30.310
- I'm fine, babe.
- This about dad?

04:30.320 --> 04:32.320
- Mm-hmm.
Why don't you go back inside?

04:32.320 --> 04:36.620
I'll tell you in a minute.

04:40.330 --> 04:43.060
He's Ted's pride, you know?

04:43.060 --> 04:45.760
He got accepted into
four Ivy league schools.

04:45.770 --> 04:47.400
That's not bad
for a son of a cop.

04:50.100 --> 04:52.240
- There should be a law
against cops getting married.

04:52.240 --> 04:54.040
- Thought they had one already.

04:55.340 --> 04:57.940
So is officer Cody
a martyr or a mook?

05:01.350 --> 05:03.780
- His ex wasn't lying
about medical bills.

05:03.780 --> 05:07.350
You got x-rays, surgeries,
meds, insurance.

05:07.350 --> 05:10.190
Second notice, third notice.

05:10.190 --> 05:12.260
Looks like he owes about
half a mil.

05:12.260 --> 05:14.430
- I had six weeks to go,
I'd make 'em wait, too.

05:19.330 --> 05:21.300
Whoa.

05:28.670 --> 05:31.710
- I'd say this is about
20 grand times two.

05:31.710 --> 05:35.080
- You're kidding.
- Hey, I used to work narcotics.

05:35.080 --> 05:39.280
- Things are starting
to lean towards mook.

05:39.290 --> 05:44.090
But since he got put on a desk,
we don't talk so much anymore.

05:44.090 --> 05:47.120
- Oh, that's nice.
But we didn't ask that.

05:47.130 --> 05:50.260
- Fine.
I was his last partner, yeah.

05:50.260 --> 05:52.400
- Where'd you work?
- North side.

05:52.400 --> 05:54.230
Lake view, Lincoln park.

05:54.230 --> 05:56.100
Blue haired ladies looking for
their lost labradoodles.

05:56.100 --> 05:57.770
Not exactly high-risk stuff.

05:57.770 --> 05:59.270
- Let me ask you this,
officer Hawkins.

05:59.270 --> 06:02.170
If I were to go to your crib,
make myself a drink,

06:02.180 --> 06:03.310
go to your freezer,
get some ice.

06:03.310 --> 06:04.780
What am I gonna find?

06:04.780 --> 06:06.310
- What is this, "jeopardy"?

06:06.310 --> 06:08.250
- Just answer the question.

06:08.250 --> 06:11.720
- My freezer?
Uh, a couple of brats,

06:11.720 --> 06:13.280
mint chocolate chip ice cream.

06:13.290 --> 06:15.720
I don't know, what?
- No cash?

06:15.720 --> 06:17.090
- What the hell
are you implying?

06:17.090 --> 06:18.790
- Your partner...
- Former partner.

06:18.790 --> 06:21.060
- He had almost
40 grand stashed away.

06:21.060 --> 06:22.360
Do you know anything about that?

06:22.360 --> 06:24.260
- No way.

06:24.260 --> 06:26.360
You wanna go through my fridge?
My underwear drawer?

06:26.370 --> 06:28.370
Help yourselves.
I got nothing to hide.

06:28.370 --> 06:30.500
If Cody was into something,
I don't know nothing about it.

06:30.500 --> 06:32.270
- When's the last time
you saw him?

06:32.270 --> 06:35.240
- The last time I said hello
was, like, two weeks ago.

06:35.240 --> 06:37.210
Truth is, dying guys
kinda give me the willies.

06:37.210 --> 06:39.480
Have a good day.

06:39.480 --> 06:42.280
- So you're ruling out his ex.

06:42.280 --> 06:44.050
- Actually, I think
she loved the guy.

06:44.050 --> 06:45.450
- Either way, she wasn't strong
enough to break his neck

06:45.450 --> 06:47.150
even if he was dying.

06:47.150 --> 06:49.120
You sure?

06:49.120 --> 06:51.820
- You know how many carcinogens
are in a hot dog?

06:51.820 --> 06:53.360
- Too late now.
- Officer Cody's

06:53.360 --> 06:55.130
former partner
is a sack of nails.

06:55.130 --> 06:57.060
Not my first choice
if I were gonna run a scam.

06:59.330 --> 07:01.100
Hang on.

07:01.100 --> 07:03.470
Nagel.
Yeah.

07:03.470 --> 07:05.270
- Seriously, though,
I don't eat meat.

07:05.270 --> 07:07.140
- Thanks, Ronnie.

07:07.140 --> 07:09.410
Ronnie ran Cody's
incoming and outgoing.

07:09.410 --> 07:12.380
He called the sack of nails
three times.

07:14.850 --> 07:16.780
- It's not what you think.
- No?

07:16.780 --> 07:18.150
Why don't you tell us
what it is?

07:18.150 --> 07:19.420
- Well, I don't know you.

07:19.420 --> 07:21.450
You come asking me questions
about some dead guy.

07:21.450 --> 07:24.160
- Telling the truth
works for me.

07:24.160 --> 07:28.460
- What were you and Cody
talking about the day he died?

07:28.460 --> 07:29.930
- Meat.

07:29.930 --> 07:31.360
- What?

07:31.360 --> 07:34.330
- This is really the story
you're going with?

07:34.330 --> 07:38.570
Cody had a standing order
at some north side butcher.

07:38.570 --> 07:41.210
Steaks, chops,
all kinds of meat.

07:41.210 --> 07:43.170
Once a month...
Because he was desked up...

07:43.180 --> 07:45.840
I would go pick it up for him
out of the kindness of my heart.

07:45.850 --> 07:48.510
- Okay.
How much meat we talking?

07:48.510 --> 07:50.510
In dollars?
- I don't know.

07:50.520 --> 07:54.150
A lot. A couple a grand.
- On a cop's salary?

07:54.150 --> 07:56.250
- All I know is I would
walk in the front door

07:56.260 --> 07:57.860
and they would hand me
a couple of cartons.

07:57.860 --> 07:59.490
It was totally legit.

07:59.490 --> 08:03.530
- I just assumed Cody
was in tight with the owner.

08:03.530 --> 08:05.230
He'd get the meat at a discount

08:05.230 --> 08:06.560
and sell it to the guys
for a profit.

08:06.570 --> 08:08.430
- All due respect,
if it was all legit,

08:08.430 --> 08:10.270
why did you lie about it?

08:10.270 --> 08:11.370
- You know it is against regs

08:11.370 --> 08:13.500
to do personal business
on city time.

08:13.510 --> 08:15.540
I didn't need the bosses
coming down on me.

08:15.540 --> 08:16.970
- We're gonna talk
to this butcher, Hawkins.

08:16.980 --> 08:19.880
So help me, if you're lying...
- who is he?

08:19.880 --> 08:21.510
- Beckett's meats.

08:21.510 --> 08:24.420
It's over on, um...

08:24.420 --> 08:25.850
- I know where it is.

08:34.230 --> 08:35.429
- John Beckett.

08:35.429 --> 08:37.289
- The one and only.

08:37.299 --> 08:39.360
- What am I missing?

08:42.299 --> 08:44.440
- Five years ago...

08:44.440 --> 08:48.010
Beckett owns a small farm
and meat packing warehouse.

08:48.010 --> 08:50.470
He is up to his eyeballs
in debt.

08:50.480 --> 08:52.610
So he does what
any thinking man does.

08:52.610 --> 08:54.280
- Burns it all down.

08:54.280 --> 08:56.250
- For the insurance.
- He killed a lot of pigs,

08:56.250 --> 08:58.250
a whole bunch of chickens,
but more importantly,

08:58.250 --> 08:59.420
a farmer sleeping in the barn.

08:59.420 --> 09:03.320
- His name was Paul Marcus.

09:03.320 --> 09:05.390
- Okay.

09:05.390 --> 09:07.460
So that's felony murder,
not to mention

09:07.460 --> 09:09.290
numerous animal cruelty
felonies.

09:09.300 --> 09:12.460
- That's why I arrested him.
- Beckett's attorney

09:12.470 --> 09:15.570
argued that the fire was started
by an electrical short.

09:15.570 --> 09:18.300
- Fire marshal swore
up and down it was gasoline.

09:18.300 --> 09:19.900
- The jury deliberated
for four days.

09:19.910 --> 09:21.540
Four damn days.

09:21.540 --> 09:24.510
And then they acquitted
the son of a bitch.

09:26.980 --> 09:30.350
- I doubt Beckett was just being
nice to an ailing copper.

09:30.350 --> 09:32.480
- Go talk to him.

09:32.490 --> 09:34.320
- Gladly.

09:47.000 --> 09:49.970
- Johnny Beckett.

09:49.970 --> 09:52.270
- Detective Dawson, right?

09:52.270 --> 09:53.970
- It's sa investigator, now.

09:53.970 --> 09:56.610
This is investigator nagel.

09:56.610 --> 09:59.640
- Well, I realize we have
a special relationship,

09:59.650 --> 10:01.980
but for retail, you're gonna
have to go to the shop.

10:01.980 --> 10:04.680
- We're here about
cpd officer Ted Cody.

10:04.680 --> 10:07.020
- Who?
- He spent $2,000 a month

10:07.020 --> 10:08.090
in your store.

10:08.090 --> 10:10.720
- Yeah? A lot of people
spend more.

10:10.720 --> 10:13.460
- How many of them end up
murdered in a bathtub?

10:13.460 --> 10:15.130
- Are you accusing me
of something?

10:15.130 --> 10:17.290
- Breathing.

10:17.300 --> 10:19.300
- Cody lived alone.
He was dying.

10:19.300 --> 10:21.100
I doubt he'd be eating
that much meat.

10:21.100 --> 10:22.670
- Well, it's the best meat
in the city.

10:22.670 --> 10:25.100
- He was flush with cash,
hidden in his freezer.

10:25.100 --> 10:26.740
- Where the meat should've been.

10:26.740 --> 10:30.010
Did you talk to
the jolly green giant?

10:30.010 --> 10:31.310
- Screw you, Beckett.

10:31.310 --> 10:34.410
- Hey, the state and the feds
already have.

10:34.410 --> 10:37.410
Every time I turn around,
you people got a new regulation.

10:37.420 --> 10:40.080
- What's that gotta do
with Ted Cody?

10:40.090 --> 10:43.390
- So now what?
You're accusing me of murder.

10:43.390 --> 10:45.720
Again.

10:45.730 --> 10:48.330
Look, I already told you.

10:48.330 --> 10:50.390
I don't know officer Cody.

10:50.400 --> 10:52.500
But I am sorry
for the city's loss.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.060
Now I gotta get back to work.

10:54.070 --> 10:56.070
You wanna look around,
help yourself.

10:56.070 --> 10:59.100
Just, uh, watch where you step.

10:59.110 --> 11:00.740
Those look like nice shoes.

11:03.040 --> 11:06.110
- Guy's still an ass wipe.

11:06.110 --> 11:07.480
- I wonder if there's
a bar around here.

11:07.480 --> 11:10.510
- Yeah, that guy? I can use one.
- Not for us, Dawson.

11:10.520 --> 11:12.350
Alcohol in Cody's blood?

11:12.350 --> 11:14.490
There wasn't
a minibar in his room.

11:19.520 --> 11:21.490
- What can I get for you folks?
- Nothing for us.

11:21.490 --> 11:24.130
- Okay. What can I do for you?
- You ever seen this guy?

11:24.130 --> 11:27.060
- Yeah, a couple days ago.

11:27.070 --> 11:28.300
- How about him?

11:28.300 --> 11:31.370
- No, I don't think so.

11:31.370 --> 11:33.470
Yeah, he was here
with the first guy.

11:33.470 --> 11:35.240
- You happen to hear
what they were talking about?

11:35.240 --> 11:38.180
- It was kinda busy, you know?
Are they in trouble?

11:38.180 --> 11:39.480
- Thanks.

11:44.120 --> 11:46.080
- I had a good reason
to lie to you.

11:46.090 --> 11:48.520
- Yeah? We're really looking
forward to hearing it.

11:48.520 --> 11:50.350
<i>- Should I call my attorney now?</i>

11:50.360 --> 11:52.120
<i>- Hey, you clean up the lie,
you won't need to.</i>

11:52.120 --> 11:53.290
- Nice.

11:53.290 --> 11:56.830
<i>- Okay. Cody's a friend.</i>

11:56.830 --> 11:59.160
<i>He called in a bad state.</i>

11:59.170 --> 12:01.230
He can't take it anymore.

12:01.230 --> 12:04.200
The cancer, the money.
He wanted there to be

12:04.200 --> 12:06.340
something left for his kid.

12:06.340 --> 12:08.840
So he tells me
he's gonna end it all.

12:08.840 --> 12:11.080
- Did he ask you for money?
- No.

12:11.080 --> 12:12.840
No, he was a proud guy.

12:12.850 --> 12:14.480
Proud and stupid.

12:14.480 --> 12:16.210
I would've given him
whatever he wanted.

12:16.220 --> 12:18.480
- Mm. Where'd you go?

12:18.480 --> 12:20.250
- Local joint called Ernie's.

12:20.250 --> 12:22.150
See, I thought maybe
what he really wanted.

12:22.150 --> 12:26.590
We shot the breeze.
I thought everything was fine.

12:26.590 --> 12:29.130
So I went back to work
at the farm.

12:29.130 --> 12:31.160
<i>- You do realize
your life would be a lot easier</i>

12:31.160 --> 12:33.160
<i>if you told us all that
from the get-go.</i>

12:33.170 --> 12:34.870
- When I heard he was dead,

12:34.870 --> 12:37.400
I thought for sure
you people would blame me.

12:37.400 --> 12:39.170
And it looks like I was right.

12:42.170 --> 12:43.770
Holy crap.

12:43.780 --> 12:46.340
The big guns, huh?
The heavy artillery.

12:46.350 --> 12:48.150
- Good to see you too,
Mr. Beckett.

12:48.150 --> 12:51.420
On that side of the table.
- Yeah, fine. I'm guilty.

12:51.420 --> 12:54.280
Guilty of honoring
a friend's last request.

12:54.290 --> 12:56.520
Keeping his confidentiality.

12:56.520 --> 12:58.560
- Cody's receipts
from your store,

12:58.560 --> 13:01.260
it didn't take Steve Jobs
to figure out they were fake.

13:01.260 --> 13:03.230
Probably cooked them up
the moment my investigators

13:03.230 --> 13:04.560
walked out of there.

13:04.560 --> 13:06.900
You were paying him off
for something in meat.

13:06.900 --> 13:08.530
- And cash.

13:08.530 --> 13:12.400
- I wanna know why.

13:12.400 --> 13:16.210
- On your mark. Get set.

13:16.210 --> 13:18.180
Call my lawyer.

13:26.150 --> 13:27.650
- Gail?

13:27.650 --> 13:30.250
- Hey, Peter.

13:30.260 --> 13:31.920
- Hey.
- Hi.

13:33.490 --> 13:36.890
- You look good.
- Eh, you don't have to lie.

13:36.900 --> 13:40.230
I'm managing.

13:40.230 --> 13:44.370
My mom saw a commercial for one
of those Christian dating sites.

13:44.370 --> 13:47.200
She thinks it's time
for me to move on.

13:47.210 --> 13:49.240
Widow with
a high school education

13:49.240 --> 13:53.180
looking for a man
who works with pigs.

13:53.180 --> 13:56.580
She doesn't understand.

13:56.580 --> 13:58.450
Paul's high school
football Jersey...

13:58.450 --> 14:01.450
The one he was wearing
the night he died...

14:01.450 --> 14:04.220
I keep it beside my bed.

14:04.220 --> 14:07.190
Can't bring myself
to get rid of it.

14:07.190 --> 14:10.530
- You shouldn't
feel guilty, Gail.

14:10.530 --> 14:13.230
- Neither should you.

14:14.700 --> 14:18.570
I received your Christmas cards.
I meant to write back, but...

14:22.440 --> 14:24.980
- something's come up.
It may not be anything,

14:24.980 --> 14:28.410
but we're investigating Beckett.

14:28.410 --> 14:29.950
- I thought you couldn't,
legally.

14:29.950 --> 14:32.380
- It's on another matter.

14:32.380 --> 14:35.350
- He burned down another farm?
- Not quite.

14:35.350 --> 14:37.220
I know it's a long shot,

14:37.220 --> 14:40.320
but do you remember
Paul ever mentioning

